brewery.brewery_description:
Lickinghole Creek Craft Brewery is a water-conscious, biologically friendly farm brewery carefully crafting Belgium-style beers and growing hops, barley and other adjuncts.

Our name pays homage to Little Lickinghole Creek, which runs through the farmâ€™s rolling hills.  Since precolonial times the creek has been known as the Lickinghole where wildlife stopped to drink from the nourishing waters.  May the tradition continue.

beer.beer_description: Belgian beer meets American and New Zealand Hops, they live happily ever after. Named after the Magic Beaver pond on the farm's property, LCCB's Pale Ale is a combination of Belgian Pilsner Malt, authentic Belgian yeast and American and New Zealand hops. Delicious and easy to drink.

Heir Apparent is an Imperial Stout with a complex caramel soul tempered by a chocolate & roasty undertone. Sweeter in style than Russian Imperial Stouts at only 60 IBUs, but balanced by the heat of fresh Mexican Peppers, Vanilla, and Cocoa Nibs. The Heir Apparent is ambitiously biding his time until he comes to power. His time will come.

Nuclear nugget is a hop bomb. It's not delicate or subtle. What it is, is a hop heads dream fulfilled. Nuclear nugget explodes with flavor of citrus flowers and strong herbal and spice notes. Bearer Farms Goochland clover honey attempts attempts to contain the Nuggets fallout, only to be radiated with dry hop nugget additions. Not intended for the faint of heart or on uninitiated. Proceed with caution. The hour draws nigh.

The Three Chopt name comes from a nearby colonial era trail marked by three hatchet marks on a tree. LCCB's Tripel is a non-stopped hopped version of a European classic. We use American grown Sterling and New Zealand Grown Motueka Hops that help impart a lemon and lime characteristic with a hint of tropical fruit. Multiple hop additions throughout the boil create a textured, full flavor.

(The base beer for the Enlightened Despot) Bold and aggressive best describe the Virginia Black Bear. Ten Specialty Grains comprise the backbone of the beer and high alpha American hops give the bear her teeth. Notes of dark chocolate and coffee abound. Used as the base beer for the Enlightened Despot, the Virginia Black Bear has escaped to wander where she wants. Beware the bear.

The Enlightened Despot is an amazingly rich, complex and surprisingly drinkable Bourbon Barrel Russian Imperial Stout.  Notes of chocolate, vanilla, and of course the delicious flavor of Pappy Van Winkle Bourbon round out this robust stout.  Aged for 100 days in 15 Year Pappy Van Winkle Family Reserve Barrels, made with 10 specialty grains and containing over 78 IBU of American Hop flavor, this truly is a one of a kind beer.

Our ode to Belgian Farmhouse Ale. The Short Pump name comes from the colonial era Short Pump Tavern, a famous mid-way point between Richmond and Charlottesville. Lickinghole Creek's Saison matches Premium Imported Belgian Pilsner Malt with two types of Rye. First Wort Hopped (an old German brewing technique) with American Grown Galena Hops and Hop Bursted (a newer American technique) with large amounts of Columbus and Nugget hops. The combination of the malt, rye and hops creates a beer with a distinguished hop aroma, a more undeviating bitterness and a more balanced beer.
Bourbon barrel version of Heir Apparent

Aged for over 3 months in Kentucky Bourbon Barrels, notes of vanilla, oak and the choicest bourbon compliment the honey and citrus notes Three Chopt Tripel is known for. Multi-layered, complex and deceptively smooth.

This 9 is a 10 in our books, because it not only tastes great, it gives back to a community in need of fresh water resouces. The taste has classic IPA bitterness on the nose, and is perfectly balanced with a citrus-like sourness on the nose which gives 9 Mile itâ€™s sessionably drinkability and fruity characteristic.
Conditioned on lime zest and aged for over 3 months in Mexican Tequila Barrels, notes of lime, oak and the smoothest tequila compliment the honey and citrus notes Three Chopt Tripel is known for.

Redneck Wedding is a Belgian- Style Quadrupel Ale aged in Kentucky Bourbon Barrels for three months. We used our house Belgian yeast strain, which adds to the complexity of the quad and Belgian Candy Syrup called D180. D-180 is a very dark, award winning premium Candi Syrup, which contributes to the depth and lightens the body of the most authentic Belgian-Style Quads. Tasting notes of raisin, plum, prune & currants & Bourbon. Bring the family and let the bad decisions ensue.

As the name suggests, Citra Fresh IPA is made to be consumed
immediately. Hopped generously with the most sought after hop on planet Earth - Citra. Citra hops impart a smooth citrus
aroma and flavor in beer. We designed a delicate and soft malt
backbone to accentuate the hop flavor and added nearly a pound and a half of Citra hops per barrel, all added near the end of the boil, to get the most flavor and aroma from the hop. It's a very freshy beer!

Made with Home Grown Rosemary. Seasonal, One Batch Brewed. Rosemary Saison is a delicious and refreshing farmhouse ale. Dry and hoppy with the perfect amount of rosemary to create a unique saison, unlike any you have had before.

This style was first brewed in the 18th century in London for export to the court of Catherine the Great, an Enlightened Despot. Enlightened Despots were absolute monarchs influenced by the Enlightenment. Illuminatos (Latin for Enlightened) is made with ten different specialty grains, generously hopped, aged in premium rum barrels for as long as it takes and cold-conditioned on fresh vanilla. The all seeing eye is nearly upon us.

Aged in Nicaraguan Flora de Cana Rum Barrels for over 12 weeks, the Batchelors Delight is a unique and delicious Belgian-Style Quadrupel Ale.

Tasting Notes:
Plum, raisin, vanilla and rum

Serve at 55 degrees and pairs exceptionally well with roasted lamb.

Name Origin:
Like all great legends the facts are in dispute. Batchlors Delight is named for one of the most notorious and important pirate ships in history. Captained by the infamous buccaneers Davis, Wafer and Hingson, who won the ship in a card game. After years of pirating in the Caribbean the trio were set on retiring in Virginia. They were arrested near Hampton Roads and spent nearly 3 years in prison. They were able to negotiate their freedom by giving up a large portion of their booty, which King William used for the "Charitable Purpose" of founding the College of William and Mary.

Pony Pasture Pilsner is a classic Bohemian Pilsner. Continental Pilsner Malt w/ a touch of Munich & Cara Malt comprise the malt structure of the beer. American grown Srerling hops were utilized for bitter & aroma additions w/ that vintage Czech Saaz addition @ 20 minutes for the noble aromatic blend of earth & spice that we love so much. Perfect for hot Virginia days down by the Rivah.

Made with hops we grew on the farm. This is a beer unique to the Commonwealth of Virginia. Very limited release. Double dry hopped. This is the beer we've been wanting to make since we began planning the brewery. Gentleman Farmer is our attempt to add terroir (the taste of place) to beer.

Four Pillars DIPA is a hop lovers dream without the harsh bitterness generally associated with the style.  We first wort hopped it with Galena for a smooth bittering addition and then Hop-Bursted it with stupid amounts of Columbus, Pacific Jade and Apollo hops for a fantastic flavor and aroma profile.  To get even more hop aroma we double-dry hopped 4 Pillars with Columbus and Apollo.

Bourbon Barrel German Chocolate Cake is LCCB's first example of a barrel aged lager. Lagers ferment for longer periods of time than ales and at much colder temperatures. Bourbon Barrel German Chocolate Cake is dark in color and deliciously innovative. Brewed with German Specialty Grains and German Hops, we aged it in Kentucky Bourbon Barrels and cold conditioned it on coconut, pecans, coco nibs and vanilla.

Chocolate Obsessionâ€™s stunning chocolate flavor derives from the combination of hundreds of pounds of chocolate malts sourced from all over the world and ridiculous amounts of South American grown cocoa nibs. Stunning chocolate flavor, full bodied and quaffable. Tastes as if it were dipped in chocolate and made to be imbibed with the one you love. Pour the bottle, turn off the lights & cue the music.

Pumpkin Ainâ€™t Easy is a refreshing take on modern Pumpkin Beers. We skipped adding Pumpkin Pie Spice to this one and let the spice notes come from the fantastic combination of our house Belgian Yeast and the deliciousness of German Tettnang and Hersbrucker hops. We thought it might be a good idea to get the pumpkin flavor from actual pumpkins so Pumpkin Ainâ€™t Easy is made with hundreds of pounds of LCCB Grown sugar pumpkins that we sliced, roasted at Tazza Kitchen, peeled and added to the mash. When we say Pumpkin Ainâ€™t Easy, we mean it.
Blueberry India Pale Ale collaboration with Three Notch'd Brewing Company
